Residents of Msholozi near White River in Mpumalanga are in shock as they watch their houses being demolished. The municipality says the residents have occupied the land and built on it illegally. The sheriff of the court executed an eviction order demolishing the structures. It is alleged that the residents invaded the piece of land belonging to the Matsafeni trust. SABC News Reporter Tumelo Machogo spoke to some residents who have expressed their frustrations. Watch the video below for more: 